# V-Kernel audit bundles pin a per-file SHA-256 in each manifest.json. On
# Windows, core.autocrlf=true rewrites LF->CRLF at checkout, which mutates the
# bytes and breaks committed-bundle verification (FileSHAMismatch). Force LF on
# all text so the working-tree bytes match the SHA-pinned (LF) bytes regardless
# of the cloner's autocrlf setting. Binary files are auto-detected and left
# untouched; the explicit rules below guard known-binary pilot payloads against
# any future EOL filter.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.pyc binary
*.bin binary
*.pcm binary
*.wav binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gz binary
*.zip binary
*.tar binary
*.db binary
